Container.Overview:
gPodder is a simple, open source podcast client written in Python using GTK+. In development since 2005 with a proven, mature codebase.&amp;#xD;
&amp;#xD;
[br][br][b][u][span style='color: #E80000;']Configuration[/span][/u][/b][br]&amp;#xD;
  [b]/config[/b] - Location of gPodder persistent config.[br]&amp;#xD;
  [b]/downloads[/b] - Location of downloads.[br]&amp;#xD;
  [b]GUAC_USER[/b] for setting a username for the gPodder desktop GUI[br]&amp;#xD;
  [b]GUAC_PASSS[/b] Password md5 hash for the gPodder desktop gui[br]&amp;#xD;
[br][b]When creating this container you first need to generate an MD5 hash of your password. You can do this by running the command: [br]&amp;#xD;
echo -n &lt;your_password&gt; | md5sum

